# Forvis Mazars Styling Guide

Professional, corporate styling consistent with Forvis Mazars brand guidelines.

## Brand Colors

**Primary Blues**: forvis-blue-500 (#2E5AAC), 600 (#25488A), 700 (#1C3667), 50 (#EBF2FA), 100 (#D6E4F5)
**Extended Blues**: #5B93D7, #132445
**Grays**: 900 (#212529), 800 (#343A40), 700 (#495057), 600 (#6C757D), 300 (#DEE2E6), 200 (#E9ECEF), 100 (#F1F3F5), 50 (#F8F9FA)
**Light Gradients**: #E0EDFB, #C7DDEF, #F0F7FD, #E5F1FB, #F8FBFE, #EEF6FC

## Typography

**Font**: Inter (from Google Fonts, in globals.css)
**Hierarchy**: h1 `text-3xl font-semibold text-forvis-gray-900`, h2 `text-2xl`, h3 `text-xl`, body `text-sm text-forvis-gray-800`, muted `text-sm text-forvis-gray-600`, label `text-sm font-medium text-forvis-gray-700`
**Weights**: 400 (body), 500 (labels), 600 (headings), 700 (emphasis)

## Gradients

Always use inline styles (not Tailwind). Use 135deg for diagonal, `to right` for horizontal, `to bottom right` for stats.

```typescript
// Primary diagonal (headers): style={{ background: 'linear-gradient(135deg, #5B93D7 0%, #2E5AAC 50%, #1C3667 100%)' }}
// Horizontal (table headers): style={{ background: 'linear-gradient(to right, #2E5AAC, #25488A)' }}
// Stats cards (dark): style={{ background: 'linear-gradient(to bottom right, #2E5AAC, #25488A)' }}
// Buttons: style={{ background: 'linear-gradient(135deg, #5B93D7 0%, #2E5AAC 100%)' }}

// Dashboard Cards (light):
