- `shadow-corporate` (subtle) - default cards, dashboard cards at rest
- `shadow-corporate-md` (medium) - dashboard cards on hover, elevated elements
- `shadow-corporate-lg` (high) - modals, dialogs
- Shared service cards: `shadow-sm` at rest, `shadow-md` on hover (lighter than main service lines)

**Radius**: `rounded-lg` (8px) default, `rounded-xl` (12px) for banners/emphasis, `rounded-full` for badges/icon containers

**Border Colors**: 
- `border-forvis-gray-200` (default cards, subtle)
- `border-forvis-gray-300` (inputs)
- `border-forvis-blue-500` (focus)
- `border-forvis-gray-100` (internal dividers in cards)
- `#2E5AAC` (emphasis borders via inline style)
- `#DC2626` (error banners via inline style)

**State Styles:**
- Hover: 
  - Standard: `hover:bg-forvis-gray-50`, `hover:text-forvis-blue-600`
  - Dashboard cards: `hover:shadow-corporate-md` (or `hover:shadow-md` for shared services)
  - Icons in cards: `group-hover:scale-110`
  - Arrows: `group-hover:opacity-100 group-hover:translate-x-1`
- Focus: `focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-forvis-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2`
- Disabled: `disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed`
- Loading: `animate-spin rounded-full h-8 w-8 border-b-2 border-forvis-blue-500`

## Z-Index Layering

Dashboard cards use a specific z-index hierarchy for proper layering:

```typescript
// Card container
className="relative overflow-hidden"  // Establishes stacking context

// Hover overlay (behind content)
<div className="absolute inset-0 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100" {...} />
// No z-index needed (defaults to z-0)

// Card content (above overlay)
<div className="relative z-[1]">
  {/* All content here */}
</div>

// Loading overlay (above everything)
<div className="absolute inset-0 z-10 bg-white bg-opacity-90">
  <div className="animate-spin..." />
</div>
```

**Z-Index Scale:**
- Default/Overlay: z-0 (no class needed)
- Card content: z-[1] (above hover overlays)
- Loading states: z-10 (above all card content)
- Modals: z-50 (global overlay)

**Key Rules:**
- Parent element must have `relative` and `overflow-hidden`
- Hover overlays don't need explicit z-index (stay at z-0)
- Content wrapper needs `relative z-[1]` to appear above overlay
- Loading overlays need z-10+ to cover everything

## Accessibility & Responsive

**Focus**: Always `focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-forvis-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2`
**Contrast**: WCAG AA - text on white use gray-700+, text on blue-500 use white
**Screen Reader**: `className="sr-only"` for hidden content, ARIA labels for icons

**Breakpoints**: sm (640px), md (768px), lg (1024px), xl (1280px), 2xl (1536px)
**Mobile-First**: `flex flex-col md:flex-row`, `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2`, `hidden md:block`

## Key Rules

**Inline Styles vs Tailwind:**
- **Use Inline Styles**: Gradients, brand hex colors (#2E5AAC), emphasis borders, semi-transparent backgrounds, dynamic grid templates
- **Use Tailwind**: Spacing/sizing/layout, typography (except hex), responsive, state variants, forvis-* palette colors, shadows

**CSS Classes**: Prefer predefined (globals.css): `.btn-primary`, `.btn-secondary`, `.card`, `.card-hover`, `.input-field`, `.animate-fadeIn`, `.animate-scaleIn`

**Best Practices:**
1. Use defined color palette only
2. Standard spacing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32px)
3. Inter font, defined text sizes
4. Corporate shadows only
5. Borders: gray-200/300 subtle, border-2 + #2E5AAC emphasis
6. Transitions: Always include (200ms default for dashboard cards, 200-300ms for others)
7. Focus states: Required for accessibility
8. Responsive: Mobile-first approach
9. Gradients: Inline styles, 135deg diagonal, `to right` horizontal
10. White text on gradients always
11. Dashboard cards: Light gradients (#F0F7FD to #E0EDFB) with hover overlays
12. Interactive elements: Use `group` class for coordinated hover effects
13. Loading states: Use semi-transparent overlays (bg-opacity-90) with spinner
14. Icons in cards: Scale on hover (scale-110), transition-transform 200ms
15. Arrow indicators: Fade in and translate on hover (opacity-0 → opacity-100, translate-x-1)

**Avoid:**
- Arbitrary values (except gradients/brand colors)
- New color schemes
- Default Tailwind shadows
- Bold everywhere (font-bold on gradients, font-medium on standard)
- Inconsistent spacing
- Tailwind for gradients
- Black text on gradients
- Heavy borders everywhere (except emphasis: border-2 with #2E5AAC)
- Dashboard cards without hover effects (always include hover overlay + shadow elevation)
- Forgetting z-index layering on cards with overlays (overlay needs lower z than content)
- Mixing shadow styles (use shadow-corporate for main cards, shadow-sm for compact cards)

**Core Principle**: Gradients prominent (headers, stats, emphasis, dashboard cards), Brand blue central (#2E5AAC), Visual hierarchy through gradients (darker = important), Grid-based layouts (CSS Grid for tables and dashboard cards), Professional aesthetic (clean, corporate), Interactive feedback (hover effects, loading states, transitions), Accessibility maintained (focus states, color contrast, semantic HTML).

## Dashboard-Specific Patterns

**Card Interaction Pattern:**
1. Base: Light gradient background (#F0F7FD to #E0EDFB)
2. Hover: Subtle blue overlay (rgba 0.06-0.08 opacity) fades in
3. Icon: Scales to 110% on hover
4. Title: Changes from gray-900 to blue-600
5. Arrow: Fades in (opacity-0 to 100) and translates right (translate-x-1)
6. Shadow: Elevates from shadow-corporate to shadow-corporate-md
7. Duration: All transitions 200ms for consistent feel

**Loading States:**
- Use absolute positioned overlay with bg-opacity-90
- Center spinner with flexbox
- Always z-10 or higher
- Apply rounded corners matching parent container

**Stats Display:**
- Large numbers: text-2xl font-bold
- Active/primary stat: text-forvis-blue-600
- Secondary stat: text-forvis-gray-900
- Label: text-sm text-forvis-gray-600
- Layout: flex gap-6 for horizontal, grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 for cards

**Section Grouping:**
- Main service lines: No container, direct grid
- Shared services: Nested in darker gradient container (#E0EDFB to #C7DDEF)
- Section headers: text-xl font-semibold with descriptive text-sm below
